<?xml version='1.0' standalone='yes'?>
<!DOCTYPE PLUGIN [
  <!ENTITY name      "ShipLog">
  <!ENTITY slug      "shiplog">
  <!ENTITY author    "junkerderprovinz">
  <!ENTITY version   "2026.06.16.7">
  <!ENTITY launch    "Settings/ShipLog">
  <!ENTITY gitURL    "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/junkerderprovinz/shiplog/main/plugin">
  <!ENTITY pluginURL "&gitURL;/&slug;.plg">
  <!ENTITY pkgURL    "https://github.com/junkerderprovinz/shiplog/releases/download/plugin-&version;">
  <!ENTITY emhttp    "/usr/local/emhttp/plugins/&slug;">
  <!ENTITY plgPath   "/boot/config/plugins/&slug;">
  <!ENTITY txz       "&slug;-&version;-x86_64-1.txz">
]>

<PLUGIN name="&name;"
        author="&author;"
        version="&version;"
        launch="&launch;"
        pluginURL="&pluginURL;"
        icon="anchor"
        min="6.10.0"
        support="https://forums.unraid.net/topic/shiplog">

<CHANGES>
Shows the changelog of your installed Docker containers, right in the Docker tab:
what changed from your running image to the newest, with a risk badge. Read-only —
optional AI summaries (Ollama) and Matrix alerts.

### 2026.06.16.7
- A Changelog control now shows on EVERY container, not only ones with an update:
  up-to-date containers open the release notes of the version you're running
  (grey dot). Containers with an update keep the coloured risk dot + "what
  changed". (A GitHub token is recommended so the notes resolve for more images.)

### 2026.06.16.6
- Fix the daemon dying after a restart/update: stop now waits for the engine to
  fully exit (its graceful shutdown raced the restart and left the new instance
  unable to bind the port). This is why the status page and the per-container
  chips disappeared after an update.

### 2026.06.16.5
- Bubble follows Unraid's theme (light/dark) and language (DE/EN).
- Shorter plugin description.

### 2026.06.16.4
- Add a short plugin description (shown here in the Plugins page).

### 2026.06.16.3
- Fix false "update available" on every container: the engine compared the local
  image config id against the registry MANIFEST digest, which never match. It now
  reads the running image's manifest digest (RepoDigests), so a digest update is
  only reported when the image truly moved. (This also means real updates now
  surface a changelog to summarise.)
- Settings: a "Check" button for Matrix too (tests homeserver + token live).

### 2026.06.16.2
- Plugin now shows as "ShipLog" in the Plugins list (display name; on-disk slug
  stays lowercase).

### 2026.06.16.1
- Matrix notifications wired up: a message when a new update is first sighted
  (deduped via the store; off unless MATRIX_* are set). Startup logs whether the
  token works.
- Settings page redesigned with cards, and a "Check" button next to the Ollama
  model to test reachability + that the model exists, live, before Apply.

### 2026.06.16
- AI summaries (Ollama) are now actually wired up: when configured, each
  changelog is condensed into "what changes / breaking / risk" in the bubble.
  Startup logs whether Ollama is reachable and the model is present.
- Bubble shows the newest release version (not just "latest") and the last
  release date.
- Settings page redesigned (header + grouped sections) and fixed (it rendered
  blank before).
- GitHub button always links to the repo's main page (derived even when the
  container has no OCI source label).

### 2026.06.15.1
- Engine: accept two-part version tags (e.g. OpenHands "0.18"); newest release
  is no longer hidden when a project doesn't use three-part tags.
- Bubble: GitHub button moved into a sticky header (always visible); it links to
  the repo's main page instead of a broken compare URL.
- Docker-tab control sits on its own line so it no longer stretches the status text.

### 2026.06.15
- First plugin release: read-only changelog/risk control in the native Docker tab.
- Bundles the ShipLog engine and runs it as a host daemon (no separate container).
</CHANGES>

<!--
  The package (engine binary + plugin files) is built by plugin/pkg_build.sh and
  attached to the GitHub release "plugin-&version;". SHA256 is injected at release.
-->
<FILE Name="&plgPath;/&txz;" Run="/sbin/upgradepkg --install-new">
  <URL>&pkgURL;/&txz;</URL>
  <SHA256>f7f25aa582ae5d9902449b8c94d6a741133332bc5ad98838cc8bdf01f10860f8</SHA256>
</FILE>

<!-- Post-install: (re)start the engine daemon immediately, no reboot needed. -->
<FILE Run="/bin/bash">
<INLINE>
chmod +x &emhttp;/bin/shiplog &emhttp;/scripts/rc.shiplog &emhttp;/event/* 2>/dev/null
&emhttp;/scripts/rc.shiplog restart
echo ""
echo "ShipLog &version; installed — open Settings &gt; ShipLog, or the Docker tab."
</INLINE>
</FILE>

<!-- Remove: stop the daemon, drop the package + files, keep user data + cfg. -->
<REMOVE>
<INLINE>
&emhttp;/scripts/rc.shiplog stop 2>/dev/null
removepkg &slug; 2>/dev/null
rm -rf &emhttp;
rm -f &plgPath;/*.txz
echo "ShipLog removed (appdata + settings kept)."
</INLINE>
</REMOVE>

</PLUGIN>
